This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human recognition using point clouds captured by LiDAR. It also involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with LiDAR data, which is commonly used in robotics for mapping and localization. 

Machine learning (cs.LG) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the use of deep neural networks for human recognition. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves the generation of artificial data using a human model. 

Finally, computer graphics (cs.GR) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the generation of realistic artificial data using a human model and a background.
